description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you live in Buckinghamshire and seek an opportunity to advance your nursing career within a role that will help develop your professional decision making and skills. Why not try this new opportunity and join the Amersham Community Nursing Team (ACHT).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve working with healthcare assistants and clinicians to provide nursing interventions to patients in their home environment, maximising their independence and providing care to avoid hospital admission as well as facilitating discharges from the acute. We have a full time opportunity available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experienced and newly qualified staff nurses will be considered for the post .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be innovative in your approach and willing to work with other members of the integrated team and ward staff to ensure a high quality service delivery. You must be willing to develop your own knowledge and skills, you will be supported in your personal development with training to extend your community nursing skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides a 24 hour/ 7 days a week service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Waller Community Team Lead on 07919627665&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;karen.waller@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
